{
  "text": "n the past, surveillance to detect persistent or recurrent differentiated thyroid carcinoma did not include sensitive serum thyroglobulin (Tg) assays or neck ultrasonography (US) by experienced thyroid cancer observers. Thus, many patients appeared to be cured by initial therapy of total thyroidectomy (with or without lymph node dissection) and radioiodine remnant ablation (RRA) only to have recurrent disease discovered years later [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
